{"key":"post-9809808","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9809808</id>\n<content>It should be OK.&amp;nbsp; I usually fill the PC about half way full of water when I sterilize agar, because it helps prevent boilover as the PC cools.&amp;nbsp; The antibiotic agar will be fine.&amp;nbsp; I always keep a can of it around for cloning, but use regular agar for most uses, because I actually want to see if I have bacteria present, so I can take extra care to get it cleaned up.&amp;nbsp; You can use a bit less of the powder next time.&amp;nbsp; I use about 3 1/2 tablespoons of FP agar for three cups of water, which is slightly less than called for, but does fine.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Pour your dishes when the bottle has cooled off enough to handle with latex gloves and not burn yourself.&amp;nbsp; If you wait too long, it gets thick and can't be poured easily, and if you pour too soon, it causes excess condensation in the dishes.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9810822</next>\n<prev>9809537</prev>\n<first>9809374</first>\n<last>10098985</last>\n<when>1234834028</when>\n<utime>02/17/09 03:27 AM</utime>\n</post>"}